    {
      "id": "2dtZNBrcM6ZsuB49AJmu9",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 964.6754782134565,
      "y": 52.45224844708797,
      "width": 316.1596984863281,
      "height": 180,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 403021647,
      "version": 687,
      "versionNonce": 665343222,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774927418285,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Deploying a separate Lambda for each\nhandler would allow for individual scaling.\nBut I don't think the benefits of\njustify the extra complexity over scaling\na single Lambda. The single Lambda also\nhas benefits when the warm container\nreuses the DynamoDB client across\nrequests, reducing latency and\nconnection overhead.",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "wJgW0UyygL1Koeev05YYJ",
      "originalText": "Deploying a separate Lambda for each handler would allow for individual scaling. But I don't think the benefits of justify the extra complexity over scaling a single Lambda. The single Lambda also has benefits when the warm container reuses the DynamoDB client across requests, reducing latency and connection overhead.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
